  "texts": [
    "Model trainingAfter training with contrastive learning, we removed the projection head g(.) and used e(.)",
    "it as a pre-trained feature extractor.",
    "We used a pre-trained 1D-CNN encoder to encode the SMILES strings of drugs from the Drugbank.",
    "We then trained a fully(3) L(θ |X) = - 1 n n i=1 logP(Y = y i |x i; θ) = - 1 n n i=1 y i log f (x i; θ)connected neural network to predict the side effects associated with each drug pair.",
    "For each drug pair in Drugbank, the pre-trained molecular representations were concatenated and fed to the classifier."
  ],
